snippet.textDisplay: My theory: The natives coaxed the colonists with food and promises of peace, then killed and ate them burning the bones. Those who escaped had no time to collect belongings before they fled oversea. They may have died at sea because of their small boats, or they may have sucessfully relocated. Some were killed on land while trying to leave messages, hence the bones and incompletion. The natives then stole back the goods the Europeans had taken/brought. John White tried to understand what had happened and came up with many theories of his own which is why he used invisible ink to mark a possibility.
